  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The hemolysis model employs the power-law damage accumulation integral (Giersiepen-Wurzinger formulation), whose derivation assumes a linear superposition of sub-lethal shear exposures — i.e., cumulative damage accumulates additively and independently across fluid pathlines. This linearity precondition is explicitly invoked to justify aggregation of exposure histories across the impeller passage. Validation against a single steady-state operating point (4 L/min, 3000 RPM) confirmed acceptable agreement at that condition; however, the COU spans five flow-speed combinations including transient ramp-up regimes where non-linear erythrocyte memory effects may invalidate the linearity assumption.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
