      "name": "Steady-state hemolysis validation at 4 L/min, 3000 RPM",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in-vitro measurements from the FDA benchmark dataset at the nominal operating point (4 L/min, 3000 RPM). Predicted NIH = 0.0041 mg/100 L versus measured NIH = 0.0044 mg/100 L; relative error 6.8%, within the 15% acceptance threshold. This single-point validation confirms model fidelity under steady laminar-dominated flow but does not probe the linearity assumption of the damage accumulation integral across the broader COU operating envelope.",
      "passedCriteria": true,
      "quantitativeResult": "NIH relative error = 6.8% < 15% acceptance threshold at nominal operating point"
