      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Relative error between predicted and measured NIH < 15% at validation operating point.",
      "rationale": "NIH relative error of 6.8% at 4 L/min, 3000 RPM satisfies the 15% threshold. Validation is performed at a single steady-state operating point representative of the nominal COU condition. The linearity assumption of the Giersiepen-Wurzinger model is implicitly satisfied at this single point because exposure history is monotonically increasing; however, no validation result examines whether linear superposition holds across the full five-point COU envelope, particularly at off-nominal transient ramp conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (NIH and relative hemolysis index RH) must be directly linked to the clinical decision criterion.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the primary FDA-recognized hemolysis metric for blood-contacting devices. RH < 1 acceptance criterion directly maps to the regulatory decision of non-inferiority relative to predicate device. Both QoIs are standard outputs of the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model integrated along Lagrangian pathlines."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry, fluid, and operating conditions must be sufficiently similar to COU to support extrapolation of credibility evidence.",
      "rationale": "Validation uses the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry identical to the COU device. Blood analog fluid (glycerol-water) matches COU viscosity within 4%. Validation operating point (4 L/min, 3000 RPM) falls within the COU envelope. Note: validation covers only one of five COU operating points; the power-law linearity assumption that enables interpolation across all five points is stated but not independently verified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this factor.",
      "rationale": "Per ASME V&V 40 Table 3, numerical solver error beyond code verification is not required at MRL 2. Scoped out of this assessment."
    },
    {
