    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are not assessed, consistent with MRL 2 requirements per ASME V&V 40 Table 3. The CFD model demonstrates acceptable fidelity at the nominal validation operating point (NIH error 6.8%). The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model with linear damage superposition is accepted as the regulatory standard formulation. The assessment team concludes that the model is credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions across the five COU flow-speed combinations, with RH < 1 confirmed at all five points. The overall credibility evidence is judged sufficient to support the Class II device submission decision.",
